        <div class="msgSubject">Retainer Ideas</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-20 19:16:21 | Edited: Nov 21 2010  4:06am  | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-1290302181203367859" id="quote-1290302181203367859" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-1290302181203367859" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=173&amp;mid=1290302181203367859&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=1290302181203367859&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_1290302181203367859" onclick="followToggle('add','1290302181203367859')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName " href="/users/katanaless">katanaless</a></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"></div><div class="msgWhoNum">12 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Decent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">After reading all the complaints about no AH in the game, I started to think about ways to implement something that will function almost the same as an auction house but not exactly like one. It involves retainers. I noticed that it says the Level of your retainer and started thinking. What if we could level our retainers by using them to sell items in the corresponding wards. Upon reaching certain levels, maybe allowing them to specialize in different things like Delivery, Item searching in wards, and maybe even specializing in storage. That way when extra retainers become available you can have different retainers for specific things. <br /> <br />For example, leveling a retainer to specialize in item searching would allow you to communicate with your retainer maybe using a special NPC linkshell and you give them something to search for with a min/max price range. They then search the wards for items for you. Higher retainer level in this specialization could also then improve the speed at which they find the items, or even go to different wards in other cities to search for the items you request or will allow them to find the better bargains as well. <br /> <br />With the delivery specialization, the higher level the retainer is the farther/faster it can travel to bring you the items you request from storage. This will make switching equipment for different jobs easier as you can call your retainer (using special retainer npc linkshell) to bring you the equipment you need, or help you craft things if you are not near the ward your retainer(s) are in and need certain materials in storage. Increasing level with this specialization could also increase the amount of items that can be delivered. <br /> <br />And storage specialization would increase storage capacity drastically, higher level means more storage space. <br /> <br />You could even balance this as well, like specializing will then lower different aspects of the retainer, for example if you specialize in storage then that retainer can no longer bazaar. If said retainer was a delivery retainer, then you lower their storage capacity. Things like that. <br /> <br />Just something I came up with that would be interesting to see implemented instead of just caving in and putting in an AH. This would also serve as a huge incentive to see the retainers selling items in the correct wards so they can level faster, because lets face it.. lower taxes is not really helping too much at the moment, I still see retainers with random items for sale in the wrong wards. I know it will become easier with an item search, but I would like to see some of these ideas implemented instead of just putting together an AH, because an AH can be abused as I have seen them destroy economies in different MMO's.  <br /> <br />EDIT: maybe even have a specialization for bazaar, with increased capacity in their bazaar the higher level they are. <br />Also, unrelated idea, sort of, how about a repair ward? so a crafter can then go to that ward to look for work and make it easier for people to get their equipment repaired. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 21st 2010  5:06am by katanaless </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1162876.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
